      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MADAM REACTOR (2) won at this track two runs ago before having her colours lowered at her latest appearance over 2150m at Bendigo, beaten 11 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Won't find this any harder and she can turn in a much better performance. EAGLE MAJOR (3) won two back here from a nice gate. Draws low again and is good enough to take out a race like this. AMERICAN HAMMER NZ (8) is worth plenty of thought off a last-start win by 2.75 metres at Riverina Paceway over 1740m. Can go back-to-back without surprising. MASTER MIKI (5) is worth some thought based on his victory over 1740m at Riverina Paceway two runs ago.",
